transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi there.

Speaker 1: I received a prescription in the mail today

Speaker 2: and I need to make sure I'm like not getting these sent

Speaker 1: like every so often.

Speaker 2: Okay, let me help you out with that.

Speaker 1: Can I have your phone number so I can pull up your account?

Speaker 2: Okay, phone number 616-308-6639.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much, Sam.

Speaker 2: Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 8-18-61.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: Oh, I see.

Speaker 1: Yeah, the doctor put you on refills on a monthly basis

Speaker 2: which you do not have to have them on a monthly basis.

Speaker 1: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: I don't know.

Speaker 1: I got them for future possibilities.

Speaker 2: Got it, got it.

Speaker 1: So I haven't tried it yet.

Speaker 2: Well, I'm not sure what I got that came with it actually

Speaker 1: because there was like some testosterone pills that arrived.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it looks like you did a while.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you bought 10 pills

Speaker 2: and then you did a one-time upgrade of an extra 10

Speaker 1: for $29.40 and then you also ordered

Speaker 2: a bottle of testosterone.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I'm all done getting more stuff then, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, so with your VIP status,

Speaker 1: you don't have to have your refills on a monthly basis.

Speaker 2: What a lot of people like to do is just go ahead

Speaker 1: and pause that for six months.

Speaker 2: That way it keeps your prescription active

Speaker 1: and allows you to call in whenever you need a refill

Speaker 2: and keeps you locked in at that price rate

Speaker 1: because they are gonna go up in a few months.

Speaker 2: But since you're locked in, yours would not increase.

Speaker 1: How much did I pay for mine?

Speaker 2: $63.95.

Speaker 1: Oh my, okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I could pause you until July 31st of 2026.

Speaker 1: And so at that point in time,

Speaker 2: do they just start sending them again?

Speaker 1: It would automatically send you 10

Speaker 2: unless you called to pause it further.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, I'm just gonna cancel for now.

Speaker 2: All right, not a problem.

Speaker 1: All right, you're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
